Since half of my family of four consists of two preteen boys, we go through a lot of frozen pizza.
But I have learned that this Great Frozen Pizza Shortage is a thing.
Frozen pizza sales are up by triple digits, and “every day being like Super Bowl Sunday” is how one executive described it.
Forget Toilet Paper—the Really Distressing Shortage Is Frozen Pizza, ADWEEK, April 16, 2020It makes sense, really.
Frozen pizza, among other things, is the canary in the coal mine that this lock-down’s days are numbered.